description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and experienced nurse. We are a motivated and friendly team, and we are excited to offer this fantastic opportunity to further develop acute surgical skills, whilst improving knowledge and skills in nursing leadership and management&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We work very closely with excellent teams of Clinical Nurse Specialists from the Acute Pain Service, Colorectal, Urology, Stoma Nurses and Nutrition Team that provide support and expertise to all staff members to ensure we always provide and maintain the highest standards of care for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported fully by the existing senior nursing team to develop and achieve your objectives and knowledge in this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Burstead ward supports and promotes our Trust Values of “Safe, Caring, Excellent, Together”. BTUH has been rated GOOD in the most recent Care Quality Commission visit. The ward continues to receive positive feedbacks from our nursing students and we managed to provide employment to them following their placement in the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
